Ukrainian Grain Harvest Reaches 34.1 Million Tons, Ministry Says

-- B y   D a r y n a   K r a s n o l u t s k a
-- 
2011-08-19T08:26:09Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-19/ukrainian-grain-harvest-reaches-34-1-million-tons-ministry-says.html
Ukrainian farmers reaped 34.1
million metric tons of grain as of yesterday as yields increased
from a year ago, the  Agriculture Ministry  said.  Reaping covered 11.15 million hectares (27.6 million
acres), or 99.5 percent of sown areas, the Kiev-based ministry
said in a  statement  on its website.  The average yield climbed to 3.05 tons a hectare from 2.47
tons in the previous year, according to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Daryna Krasnolutska in Kiev at 
 dkrasnolutsk@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Balazs Penz at   bpenz@bloomberg.net . 